Floated on off, Root whips it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up around off, Root leans forward and blocks it.
Flighted on off, Root defends it.
Length ball outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.

NO BALL! This one goes the other way around. Outside off on a length. Sibley does well as he keeps his eyes on the ball and leaves it alone. Oh, dear! Another no ball from India. They have been poor with their discipline. Not something you usually associate with this Kohli-led side.
Beauty! Ishant has been brilliant today. Reverse swing on offer for him. Fuller outside off, it comes back in. Sibley looks to defend but is a bit late and luckily does not get any bat on it.
Full around off, Sibley flicks it to mid-wicket.
Fuller around off, Sibley gets on his front foot and defends it. No problem with the bounce this time around.
Keeps a bit low. Good length ball on off, it comes in a bit with the angle and keeps low. Sibley adjusts to the bounce in the eleventh hour and manages to get bat on ball.
Length ball around off, Sibley blocks it.
Shorter on the pads, Root dabs in onto the ground in front of short leg.
Ishant Sharma (8-2-11-0) is back on.

FOUR! This time through the off side. Too short, very wide, and Root is in too good a form to miss out on it. He gets on his back foot and punches it through covers. There is a huge gap there and the England Test skipper hits it in that gap for a boundary. Back-to-back poor deliveries from Ashwin. You seldom see that.  Is it the sign of the spinner being tired?
FOUR! First poor ball from Ashwin and Root is quick to punish it. Short around off, too short and slightly wider from off pole. Root pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Another one which is short on off, Root gets on his back foot and defends it.
Shorter on off, Root defends it.
Short and spinning in around off. Sibley knocks it to mid off for a single.
Good running! Fuller around off, Sibley pushes it to the right of mid off and takes a quick single to keep the strike.
Angled into middle, Sibley flicks but to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it to the leg side.
Short ball from Bumrah! The effort ball. Sibley ducks under it.
Full on the pads, Root flicks it to the leg side for a single.

Appeal for LBW but turned down by the umpire. Seems like it is going down leg and hence Kohli has opted to not review it. Slower delivery on middle and leg. Root looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad. There is an appeal but the umpire is not interested. Kohli, Bumrah and Pant have a chat but the latter does not seem too keen and the Indian skipper does not review it. Good call not to review it as Ball Tracker shows it to be going down leg later on.

In the air but off the pad. Floated outside off, Sibley looks to defend but misses. The ball hits his pad and lobs to leg slip, who takes the catch. There is a muted appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Shorter on off, Sibley keeps it out.
Flights one on off, Sibley keeps it out.
Flighted on the stumps, Sibley defends it.
Shorter around the pad, Sibley tucks it to the on side.
Floated on off, Root sweeps it to square leg for a single.
On the pads, Sibley defends it to the leg side.
Wow! This is crispy from Bumrah! A leg cutter is followed by a pacy yorker on middle. Sibley does really well to get his bat down in time.
Edged but does not carry! Leg cutter on off, Sibley looks to defend but gets an outside edge which does not carry to Rohit Sharma at first slip.
Length ball on off, Sibley defends it.
NO BALL! On off, Sibley blocks it. It is another no ball as Bumrah has overstepped.
Length delivery angling in on middle. Root flicks it using the angle behind square on the leg side for one.
Good length ball on off, Root defends it.
Floated on midddle, Sibley blocks it.
Darted around the pads, Dom Sibley flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Sibley defends it.
Floated on off, Sibley blocks it.

FIFTY FOR SIBLEY! This has been a gritty knock from the English opener. A real impressive innings from Sibley. He has shown heart and courage today. Shorter on off, Sibley punches it through covers and gets a brace to bring up his fifty. It has been a well-composed innings from him/. He raises his bat as his teammates applaud his effort. He knows the job is not done though and he will look to convert this into a hundred.
Shorter on off, Sibley defends it off his back foot.
Change from both the ends now. Ravichandran Ashwin is back into the attack. 16-2-39-1 are his numbers so far.
On the pads this time, Sibley tickles this one to the fine leg region for one. Moves onto 49 with this one. Just one run away from his half-century.
Angles in a length delivery around off, Dom blocks this one out.
Outside off on a good length, way too outside the off pole for Dom to be to worried about having to play at this. Lets it be.
Good length and on off, Sibley pushes this one to the mid on region.
Length and around off, Sibley blocks this one out.
On a good length and on middle, clipped to the square leg region for a single.
Jasprit Bumrah is back on. 10-1-24-1 for him so far.
On the pads, Sibley blocks it.
On the pads, Root flicks it in front of the crease on the leg side and gets a single.
Falls just short of leg slip! On the pads, Root flicks it behind on the leg side. There is a leg slip for this shot but unluckily for Kohli and co. it falls short of the fielder there.
Shorter on off, Root defends it off his back foot.
Short around leg, Root dabs it to the leg side.
Nicely bowled. Floated around off, Root defends it towards point.

FOUR! Excellent from Sibley. Just two away now from what will be a very good and gritty fifty if he gets there. Flighted on middle, Sibley uses his wrists and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
NO BALL! Another one from Nadeem and he needs to sort these out now. Short on middle, Root flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Shahbaz Nadeem gives this a bit of air on middle. Root defends it off the inner half of his bat.
Tossed up on middle, Root defends it.
Flighted on off, Root blocks it.
FOUR! Brings up the 50-run stand. Tossed up fuller around off, Root strides forward and sweeps it in front of square for a boundary.
Flighted outside off, Root shoulders arms to it. Pant likes the pace at which this is bowled as he says it in Hindi to Nadeem.
Tossed up on off, Sibley blocks it.

FOUR! Uppish but safe! Floated on middle, Sibley brings out an aggressive sweep. There is a shout of catch it as it goes uppishly but it well away from short leg and mid-wicket. Sibley finds the gap and gets a boundary. Moves to 44 with that.
Floated on off, Sibley blocks it.
Good ball! Washington gives this a lot of air on middle and leg. Sibley looks to flick but closes the face of the bat early. The ball goes to point off the leading edge.
Floated on middle, Sibley flicks it to mid-wicket and shouts an audible no.
Darted fuller on middle and leg. Root reverse sweeps it to backward point for a single.
Shorter on off, Sibley defends it with a straight bat.
Tossed up around off, Sibley comes down the track and defends it.
Flighted on off, Sibley blocks it.
On the stumps, kept out.
Tossed up on the stumps, Sibley blocks it.

Beautifully played! Short around off, Root punches it through point. Sundar misfields and there is a yes-no for the second and they opt against it. Good call, they will not want to risk a wicket in chasing a run.
Good take from Pant! Pitched outside leg, Sibley leaves it alone. There is some extra bounce off the surface on this one. Pant takes it well as that was not an easy take.
Swept hard but there is a man at deep backward square leg. On the pads, Root sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
This time Sibley flicks it with softer hands and wide of Rohit Sharma at mid-wicket for one.
Darted full on middle and leg. Sibley flicks it to mid-wicket.
Around the pads. Root glances it to fine leg and gets to the other end. Runs starting to come frequently now for this pair.
Shorter around off, Root tucks it to the on side.
Floated on off, Sibley keeps it out.
Shorter on middle and leg. Sibley flicks it onto the ground. It hits Gill's pad at short leg.
Tossed up around off, Sibley goes back to defending.

FOUR! Excellent shot! He uses his feet to perfection there. Tossed up on off and middle, Sibley puts on his dancing shoes and plays it with a straight bat through the cow corner region for a boundary. 100 up for England as well.
Shorter on off, Sibley defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up around off, Sibley strides forward and defends it.
On the stumps, the England skipper carefully defends it.
Floated on off, Root goes back to watchfully defending it.

FOUR! Lovely shot! Root brings out the reverse sweep and unlike Burns, he plays it with perfection. Tossed up outside off, Root picks the right length and the right ball to play the shot. He hits it behind point for a boundary.
Tossed up around off, Root leans forward and blocks it.
Flatter on middle and leg, Root defends it to the leg side.
Tossed up around off, Root defends it off the outer half of his bat to point.
Tossed up on off, Sibley defends it to the right of the bowler.
Flighted on off, Sibley defends it off his front foot.
Deft touch! Short around off, Root dabs it towards third man. He looks for two but decides against it. Good call as it would have been very dangerous.
Tossed up around off, Root leans forward and defends it.
Flighted on off, Root defends it off the front foot.
Darted full on off, Root keeps it out.

DRINKS! A proper hour of Test match cricket. India kept things tight for the majority of that hour but were unable to get the wicket. Root and Sibley have battled it out in the middle. The runs had dried up but they are starting to get them now. It has been an enticing contest between bat and ball. What is in store for us in the next hour of this session?
Full and floated on middle, flicked to mid-wicket. 5 runs off Sundar's first over of the game.
Loopy and on middle, Root gets low and brings out the broom. Sweeps this one to the square leg region for a single.
On off, kept out.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
FOUR! Classy stroke from Root, who welcomes Sundar into the game with a boundary. Flighted and around off, Root moves away and creams this one through the cover region to find the fence.
Floats this one up around off, Root prods forward and keeps it out.
Sundar time! Washington Sundar is in to the attack for the first time in this game!
Loopy and around off, Root pushes this one to covers for a quick run.
Tucked to square leg with soft hands by the skipper.
On off, pushed to covers.
Down the leg side, JR misses his flick and it bounces a tad bit more than what Pant anticipated as he spills this one.
Short and around off, pushed to the off side.
Flighted on off, Root keeps this one out.
Shahbaz Nadeem is back! 5-1-11-0, his figures so far.
Floated and on off, Dom keeps this one out nicely. 4 runs off this over, courtesy Dom.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Down the leg side, left alone by Dom.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Sibley releases some pressure now for the visitors. Flighted and on middle, Sibley flicks this one through the mid-wicket region and the ball runs away to the ropes.
Flighted and on off, blocked. Kohli is heard saying 'BAHUT ACCHE ASHHH', which means 'Very good, Ash'.
Fuller and on off, Root clips this one to deep mid-wicket.
Slowish good length ball around off, Root blocks this one out towards the off side.
Length and on off, worked to the leg side.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.

EDGED...SHORT! Great bowling by Ishant. Bowls a good length ball around off, nips away slightly as Root plays this one with soft hands. It takes the outside edge and goes to Rohit on the bounce at first slip. Smart work by Joe to play it with soft hands and that is why this one did not carry to the slip.
Good length and around off, Root is solid in his defense.
Comes down the track slightly and flicks this one to deep square leg again. Maiden by Ashwin.
Blocks this one solidly off the front foot.
Loopy and on leg, clipped to deep square leg where Sundar stops this one well.
Floated on middle, flicked to short leg.
On middle, worked to mid-wicket again.
Short and on off, Sibley works this to mid-wicket.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.

An excited appeal for lbw but turned down by the umpire. A back of a length ball around off, it jags back in after hitting the deck and goes onto hit Root's pads as he misses his flick away. A loud appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Must have been high and also going down leg. Kohli and Ishant ask Pant what he thinks and he says that they probably should not take the review on this one.
Length and outside off, tapped to point.
Too straight and also moving into the right-hander, Root looks to flick but misses and the ball takes the pads and goes to Pant again.
The English skipper blocks this one nicely to the Indian skipper at the short mid-wicket region.
Back of a length and outside off, Root looks to slash this one away but the ball takes the inside edge and goes to the left of Pant.
Back of a length and on middle, Dom clips this one to the left of the deep square leg fielder for a single. Also, called as No Ball as Ishant had overstepped.
On middle, blocked out.
Screams of 'catch it' but it goes through the fielders there. Flighted and on middle, Sibley comes forward and flicks this one uppishly through the square leg region for a single.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Shortish and outside off, Dom camps back and looks to slash at this one but he does not connect bat with ball.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Ohhh...what a beauty! Ashwin comes 'round the wicket and floats this one up around the off pole, Sibley comes ahead looking to block but he misses his defensive push completely.
Length and outside off, nipping into the right-hander after hitting the deck as Root covers his sticks and the ball goes to Pant. A wry smile on Root's face after this one.
On the middle pole on a fuller length, slight inward movement noticed as Dibley whips this one to deep mid-wicket where Gill collects this one. Just the single.
Good length and on off, Sibley finds the Indian skipper, Kohli at short mid-wicket again.
Around off on a length, Sibley works this one to the gully region.
Blocks this one to the leg side, does Sibley.
Slightly behind the good length and around the off pole, Dom tucks this to short mid-wicket.
First bowling change of the session. Ishant Sharma replaces Jasprit Bumrah. 5-1-8-0, his numbers from his first spell.
Goes on the back foot and gets his bat across to fend this one out. The skipper does that successfully to see off this Ashwin over.
Joe Root has just watchfully blocked this out as well.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Flighted and on off, Root looks for the flick away and the ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes to the off side.
Flighted and outside off, Root is about to leave this one but decides to play it at the last minute. Misses and Pant collects.
Root shows off his back foot defense this time around.
Dom finds the mid-wicket fielder with his flick this time. 5 off this one.

Delightfully played by the skipper, Bumrah goes for a fuller shot and on middle, Root is able to flick this one through the mid-wicket region. By the time, Gill can run in and stop the ball, three runs are taken.
Since this is bowled closer to outside the off pole, Root defends it towards the cover region now.
An exact replica of what happened on the last ball. Root finds the short mid-wicket again.
Fires this one with the angle on the off stump, Root shuffles slightly and works this to short mid-wicket.
Good running between the wickets by these two. On a good length and on middle, Root clips this one through square leg. The batters do well to come back for the double.
Loopy around off, Dom pushes this to point. 2 runs off this over.
Another solid block offered by Sibley.
Prods on his front foot this time to defend solidly, does Dom.
On middle, clipped to the short leg fielder.
Flighted on middle, Sibley clips this one nicely through the mid-wicket region and the batters come back for the double.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
On off, played to the mid on region.

Bumrah fires in a short ball down the leg side, Root just lets it be. Pant does well to move to his left and stop this one. Called a wide first but then called as a no ball as the third umpire passes on the message.
Same sort of delivery as the last ball, Root plays the same kind of stroke. Finds the man there again.
Good length and around off, Joe taps this one towards the fielder present at gully.
Fires in a fuller ball on the middle pole, Root tucks this one but finds the square leg fielder.
Gets his bat down and blocks this one to the mid off region.
Bowls this one with the angle around the off pole, Root defends.
Loopy and around off again, Sibley tucks this one to mid-wicket.
On off, blocked by Dom.
Tossed up and around off, Root pushes this one to the cover region for a single.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Tossed up and around off, Root again comes ahead and blocks. 'Beautiful bowling, Ashwinnnn', says Virat Kohli, to appreciate his bowler.
Flighted around off, Root prods forward and keeps this one out.
Who will start the session from the other end? It will be Ravichandran Ashwin.
One run to end the over. On a length and around the off pole, Joe pushes this one through point and collects a single. Retains the strike for the next over.
Gets his bat down and blocks this one to the leg side.
Length and on off, Root pushes this one to mid on.
Outside off on a good length, stays a touch low as well, Root leaves it.
Length and around off, Root taps this one towards the cover-point region. They look for the single but then do not go for it.
Starts off with a good length delivery just outside the off pole, Root is aware of where his sticks are as he lets this one through to the keeper.

We are back for the second session of play now. The batters for England, Joe Root and Dom Sibley make their way out into the middle now. The Indian players are in a huddle near the ropes as Virat Kohli is imparting some final words of wisdom before they look to spread out on the field. Jasprit Bumrah to operate first up to begin the second session of play. He looks ready and here he comes...
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

The bowling by India was not poor but they were not rewarded for their hard work with any wickets. The pitch also was not assisting the bowlers all that much and it was slightly easy for Burns and Sibley to stroke to ball around to keep the scoreboard ticking. That is until Ashwin struck and broke this opening stand and Bumrah then sent Lawrence back into the shed for a duck. India ended the first session on top and will look to continue the same in the second session. Will they be able to do so or will Root and Sibley build something concrete? Join us for the second session shortly.

The openers for England, Sibley and Burns started off nicely. They were watchful and attacked the loose deliveries they did really well to fend off the early challenge and were looking set to head into the first break unscathed but a poor shot from Burns meant that his stay out in the middle came to an end. Lawrence then came out and went back quick as he was out plumb for a 5-ball duck. Then, there was a run out scare for Joe Root but he was safe and Sibley and Root have since managed to negotiate proceedings until Lunch.

A very intriguing session of play which hangs in the balance, you would say, as England dominated the majority of the session but towards the last half hour of the session, two quick wickets for the Indians means that this session will be shared between both these sides.
Tossed up on off, Sibley manages to keep it out. That will be the final ball of the session. Lunch on Day 1!
Floated on off, Sibley lunges and blocks it.

NOT OUT! Frantic but in the end the England Test skipper is safe. A run out here would be nothing but disastrous for England especially right before Lunch. Short on off, Root turns it to square leg and takes a single. There is a slight hesitation but they go for it. The fielder scores a direct hit at the bowler's end.The umpire takes it upstairs and replay shows it is not a direct hit but Ashwin deflected the ball onto the stumps. Anyway, Root is well inside the crease and safe.
Short around off, Root blocks it.

The third umpire is called into play for this run out appeal. Have India got another one just before the Lunch break? They will certainly hope so. Replays roll in and Root's bat is grounded before the wickets are broken. The big screen reads a big 'NOT OUT'.
Floated on off, Root blocks it.

In the air but thankfully for Root it is in the gap. Floated on off, Root looks to play it on the leg side. There is some turn and bounce for Ashwin. It takes the edge and flies through cover in the vacant region. Two taken.
Bumrah targets the stumps, Lawrence defends it with a straight bat.
Root is up and running straight away! Good length ball around off, Root taps it through point and gets off the mark with a single.

OUT! LBW! As plumb as it gets! Bumrah strikes for the first time in his Test career in India. This is a typical Bumrah delivery. Credit to Kohli as well. He has done his homework. Lawrence is a good player of spin and he easily could have continued with Ashwin after the spinner got a wicket but he introduced Bumrah and his strike bowler gives him the breakthrough. Fuller delivery pitching around off and jagging back in at pace. Lawrence looks to flick but is too late to get his bat down and the ball hits him on the backpad. Bumrah knows he has his man but puts in the mandatory appeal. The umpire has no qualms in raising the finger. Lawrence has a word with Sibley but he gets no support from him for the review. Good call because it looked plumb and the Ball Tracker later on proves it.
Two quick wickets fall for the visitors now. The skipper, Joe Root makes his way out into the middle now.
Fuller and targetting the stumps. Lawrence defends it.
Good length ball on off, Dan Lawrence defends it with a straight bat.
Good length ball outside off from Bumrah to start his new spell. Lawrence leaves it alone.
Floated on middle and off, Sibley watchfully blocks it.
Nadeem flights one on off. Sibley looks to defend and does so off the outer half of his bat.
On the stumps, kept out by Sibley.
Floated on middle and off, Sibley defends it.
Flighted on off, Sibley blocks it.
Tossed up on middle, Sibley pushes it to mid on.
Floated on the stumps, Lawrence starts his innings with a front foot defense.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ashwin gets the breakthrough and the budding, gritty opening stand has been broken. The bigger question is where has this shot come from, Rory Burns and was it even necessary in the first place? This is a Christmas gift for Ashwin from Burns which has come super early. Ashwin comes over the wicket for the southpaw and bowls a floated delivery on middle. Burns brings out the reverse sweep. The ball bounces a tad extra, kisses his glove and lobs around the stump. Easy catch for Pant who will not drop these even in his sleep. Jubilation for Ashwin and co. Disappointment for Burns.
Dan Lawrence is the new batter in at Number 3.
Flighted on off, Burns blocks it.
Tossed up on middle, Burns blocks it.
Shorter on off, Burns defends it.
FOUR! Wonderful shot! Brilliant use of the feet from Burns! Rory comes down the track and hits it wide of mid on against the spin for a boundary.
Flighted around off, kept out.
Arm ball to finish the over. It is just outside off, Sibley taps it onto the ground. Another No Ball called for overstepping.
NO BALL! Nadeem oversteps and that is criminal if you are a spinner. Floated around off, Sibley pushes it to cover.
Flighted on middle, Sibley keeps it out.
Tossed up around off, Sibley defends it to point.
Flighted on off, Sibley leans forward and defends it.
On middle, Sibley turns it to short square leg.
Floated on middle and off, Sibley defends it.
On off, kept out by RB.
Flighted on the stumps, Burns keeps it out.

FOUR! Ashwin is not finding it as easy as he would have hoped for coming back to India. Nicely played shot from Burns! Flighted delivery around off, Burns takes a big stride forward and sweeps it fine down the leg side for a boundary.
Floated on middle and off, Sibley taps it to cover for a single.
Shouts of catch it but it is away from the man at leg gully. On the pads, Sibley flicks it uppishly but away from Gill at leg gully.
Tossed up on middle, Sibley plays it short mid-wicket.
Single to end the over! Nadeem floats the last ball on the pads. Sibley is happy to turn it around to mid-wicket and keeps the strike.
Floated outside off, Sibley tucks it to short mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Sibley blocks it.
Flighted around off, Sibley defends it to point.
Shorter on off, Sibley pushes it to mid on.
Nadeem gives this one air around off. Sibley uses his tall frame as he leans forward and blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Burns is happy to watchfully negotiate it.
Flighted on off, Burns gets on his front foot and defends it.
Floated on the stumps, Burns defends it.
50 up for England. Flighted on middle, clipped to the square leg region for a couple of runs.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Flighted on off, Burns pushes it back to the bowler.
On middle, defended back by Dom.
Short and around off, pushed to the cover region.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Outside off, left alone.
Well bowled! Slows it up, it is outside off, draws the batter into playing at it. Sibley pushes it to covers.
Angled into the pads, Burns works it through square leg for one.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Flighted and on leg, flicked to short leg.
On middle, tucked to short leg.
Flatter and outside off, Burns slaps this one through the cover region and Bumrah does well to chase this one down and pull it back before the ropes. Three this time.
Another solid defense offered by Burns to this one.
Comes on the front foot and blocks.

FOUR! Sibley plays this one very well. Width on offer and he pounces. This one is fractionally short and also outside off, Sibley camps back and slaps this one through the point region to fetch the boundary.
Dom Sibley has just watchfully blocked this out.
Shorter and outside off, slapped to covers.
Flighted on off, Dom looks to block this one but the ball takes the inside edge and hits him on the pads.
Short and on middle, Burns gets on his knees and sweeps this one to the deep mid-wicket region and the fielder giving it chase does well to pull it back before the ropes. Three runs.
On off, blocked to mid-wicket.
Shahbaz Nadeem to roll his arm now.
Shortish on the stumps, Sibley knocks it to the on side.
Floated on off, Sibley keeps it out.
Flighted on middle, Sibley tucks it to the on side with the spin.
Tossed up on the stumps, Sibley blocks it.

Good running and also good fielding! Floated on off, Burns comes down the track and hits it to the right of mid off. He takes off for a quick run. Shahbaz Nadeem gets to the ball and scores a direct-hit but Burns is well in.
Floated on off, Burns blocks it.
Beauty to end the over. Bumrah bowls this on a good length area around off. Sibley looks to defend but the ball shapes away and beats the outside edge of Sibley's bat.

Almost a Bumrah special. He bowls a dipping low full toss around off, Burns manages to push it to mid off for a single. NO BALL! It has been caught by the T.V. umpire. Second no ball of the day. One by Ishant and now by Bumrah.
Length ball on middle and off, Sibley flicks it to the on side and gets a single.
On middle and off, Burns shuffles in his trademark style and flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Good length delivery around off, Burns taps it to point.
Length ball around off, Burns tucks it to square leg. He looks for a run but Sibley is quick to turn him down.
Good length ball around off, Burns flicks it straight to the man at catching short mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Sibley blocks it.
Tossed up on middle, Sibley flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up on the stumps, Sibley defends it.
Shorter on off, Sibley defends it off his back foot.

FOUR! Good shot! Sibley is looking good out in the middle. Floated delivery on middle and leg, Sibley gets on his front foot and flicks it through mid-wicket. Rohit Sharma gives it a chase and puts in a slide too but the ball beats him to the fence.
Flighted on off, Sibley flicks it to short mid-wicket with the spin.

Excellent running! Fullish ball on off and middle. Sibley gently pushes it to the left of mid on. The batters call for a quick run. Ishant charges to the ball and sends a wild throw at the keeper's end. Pant behind the stumps does well to stop it.
Nicely defended! Full outside off, Sibley gets on his front foot and blocks it.
Full around off, Burns looks to play it towards mid on. The ball goes off the outer half of his bat through point for a single. Nadeem does well to stop the ball.
Good length delivery outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Full on off, Burns defends it to mid off.
Fuller on off and middle, Sibley flicks it away from short mid-wicket for a single.

DRINKS! A very good hour of play for the tourists. The pair of Sibley and Burns have managed to get through the first hour of this game unscathed. India have bowled well but have not got the reward so far. They will be looking to get that right in the next hour of this session. Can Sibley and Burns see off the next hour as well?
EDGY SINGLE. Sibley takes one on the last ball. Flighted on off, Sibley looks to tuck this one to the leg side but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards point for one run.
Tossed up and on middle, DS fends this one out.
On middle, clipped to the leg side.
Dom comes on the front foot and keeps this one out.
Slightly short and on leg, tucked to square leg this time.
Flighted around off, Dom keeps this one out.
Rory defends this one solidly off the front foot.
Outside off, left alone.

Good length and on middle, clipped to the deep square leg region where Nadeem runs to his right and looks to stop this one and does so with his boot. He pushes the ball out of play and the batters take three. The umpires want to confirm this and concur with the third umpire. Replays roll in and it is seen that it is a clean save. Three runs.

Overthrows and a single. On a length and on off, Rory pushes this one to covers and looks for the single. Dom sends him back. Nadeem runs in and takes the ball and has a shy at the striker's end but misses as Rory puts in a dive. There is no one backing up and so the batters can take on run there.
Bumrah slips this one down the leg side, Burns looks to flick but misses this one.
EDGY. On a good length and around off, Sibley looks to defend this one but the ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes through the slip cordon for one run.
Bowling change. Jasprit Bumrah is back in action. He comes from the other end now as he replaces Ishant Sharma. 3-1-4-0, his figures from his first spell.
On middle, kept out.
Outside off, Burns is aware of his off pole as he lets this one through.
Bowls this around leg, spins back in slightly as Burns comes forward and fends this one out.
Loopy on off, Rory comes on his front foot and blocks.
Comfortable couple this time. On middle, Burns goes back slightly and clips this one through square leg. Comes back for the second run as well.
Tossed up and around off, Rory keeps it out.

Bit of hesitation for the single but they get it in the end. On a length and on off, Burns tucks this one to square leg and the batters have a bit of yes-no again. But they go for it and complete it in the end. 2 off this over. A steady start by England so far.
On a good length and on middle, enough for Dom to flick it through square leg for a single.
Bumper on middle, Dom ducks under this one well.
On a length and around off, Dom pushes this one to the cover region again. Sibley raises his blade and yells a loud 'NO RUN, NO RUNNNN' to Rory.
Gets his bat down and blocks this one to the mid on region.
Length and around off, Sibley pushes this one to covers.
Flighted on middle, Burns defends this one out. 6 runs off Ashwin's first over.
Flat and around off, spins back in after hitting the deck slightly, Sibley goes on his back foot and clips this one through square leg for one more run.
On off, tucked to the leg side yet again.
On middle, flicked to the leg side.

FOUR! First boundary for the English Lions and SIbley is the one who supplies this one. Short and wide outside off, Sibley goes on his back foot and slaps this one through backward point to fetch a boundary.
Floated on middle, Burns prods forward looking to block this one but the ball takes the inner half of the blade and goes through square leg for a single.
First bowling change of the game. Spin into the attack now as Ravichandran Ashwin is all set to operate.
On a good length and on off, Sibley pushes this one to the left of the mid on fielder. Back-to-back maidens for the Indians.
Outside off, left alone this time around by Dom.
Sibley tucks this one to the short mid-wicket fielder yet again.
On middle, clipped to the fielder present at short mid-wicket.
On a good length and outside off, DS blocks.
On a length and around off, Dom pushes this one to point. There is a bit of yes-no regarding the single but nothing results of it.
A dot to end and Bumrah gets a maiden. On a length and around off, Rory keeps it out.
Bowls a full toss around off, Burns works this one towards Gill at mid on.
Slightly behind that good length area, closer to off, Burns tucks this one but finds the fielder stationed at square leg.
Rory has just watchfully blocked this out.
Drags his length back and bowls a bumper on middle and leg, Burns sits under this one. 'BOWLING, JASSSSSI', is that the Indian players are chattering around, to show their support to Bumrah.
Gets his bat down and defends this one to mid-wicket.

BEAUTYYY! A jaffa to end with from Sharma. A wry smile on his face after this delivery. On a good length and around off, straightens a touch after hitting the deck as Dom looks to block this one out. Misses and the ball whizzes past the outside edge to Pant.
Slightly closer to the off pole on a good length, but still not enough to trouble Dom who raises his willow and lets this one through to Pant.
Around off on a length, tucked to the leg side.
Comes around slightly slower and on off, Sibley pushes this one to the cover-point region. 'No run' is the early call from Dom. Also, no ball called for overstepping.
On a good length and around that fourth stump channel, Sibley will leave this one in his sleep. Does the same while he is awake too.
On a good length and around the off pole, Sibley works this one towards the mid on region.
Closer to the off stump and around off, Dom offers a solid defense.
Does what he did on the previous delivery on this one as well. Ends the over with a dot. 3 runs off this over.
As this one is in the channel outside the off pole, Rory has no problems in letting this one go.
Hops and blocks this one towards mid-wicket. 'NO RUNNNNN', says Burns, to Sibley, in regard to the single.
Two this time. Length and on middle, Burns clips this one to the fine leg region and the openers for the English Lions come back for the second run as well.
Just outside the off pole and on a fuller length, Burns has no issues in leaving this one alone.
Quick early call and good running. A length ball on off, Dom dabs this one to the point region and calls Rory for the single. Burns replies and they complete this one nicely.
Dom is off the mark now! On a length and around off, Sibley pushes this one to the covers for a quick run.
Closer to the off pole on a length, Dom taps this one to point. Says a loud 'no' for the single.
In that channel outside off, Sibley makes no attempt to play at this. Has not opened his account yet here, has Sibley.

Sharma bowls a good length ball on middle, Burns flicks this one through the mid-wicket region and Sundar and Ashwin give it chase. Sundar does well to pull it back before the ropes. Saves one run for his side. Three runs taken.
Bowls this one with the angle around the off pole, Burns fends this one out.
Fuller and outside off, Burns raises his blade and lets this one through to the keeper.
Back of a length and around off, Dom pushes this one to the leg side. Bumrah's first over sees him concede just a single run too.
On a length and around off, Sibley blocks this one solidly.
Similar to the last delivery, the ball hits the deck and moves inwards slightly as Dom makes another leave.
Another length delivery outside off, Sibley, again, offers no shot to this one.
Good length and outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.

DROPPED? Looks like it. Pant have to stretch but he does not take this one. Good effort from him. On a length and on sliding down leg, Burns looks to tuck this one but is only able to manage a faint tickle as Pant dives to his right, gets his fingertips to this but is not able to hold on. One run for Rory.
Who will bowl from the other end with the new ball? No surprises here as Jasprit Bumrah shares the new ball with Ishant Sharma.
Good length and on the off pole, Dom plays this one towards mid on again. A tidy start by Ishant. Just the single run off this over.
Makes Dom play at this one as he bowls it close to the off pole on a good length, Sibley defends this one towards the mid on region.
Identical to the last delivery this time and Sibley offers the same shot as he did on the last ball. Which is basically no shot.
Comes 'round the wicket to the right-handed Sibley. Dishes a good length delivery outside the off pole, Sibley just leaves this one alone.
First runs of the morning and England along with Burns open their account now. A good length ball on middle, Burns clips this one to the fine leg region for a single.
Sharma starts off with a good length delivery around off, Burns gets his bat down and keeps this one out solidly.

Right then. We are done with all the pre-match formalities as the action is all set to begin. The Indian players spread out on the field. The openers for England, Dom Sibley and Rory Burns follow them out now. They will want to provide a good platform early on. Ishant Sharma to speed in with the ball. Here he comes...

Both sets of players along with the umpires walk out to the middle for their respective national anthems. First up it will be the tourists, England followed by India's. We are just moments away from the start of this exciting clash.

PITCH REPORT -  Nick Knight and Deep Dasgupta are the pitch analysts for the day. Nick Knight says that the pitch looks fresh as cricket has not been played here for a long time. Deep Dasgupta reminds us that the last time India played a Test here was in 2016 and they scored 700 runs. He though adds this does not look like a 700-run wicket. There are a few spots on the deck and every time the ball hits these areas, it could behave slightly differently. Ends by saying that it could be a two-paced wicket.

India (Playing XI) - Rohit Sharma, Shubman Gill, Cheteshwar Pujara, Virat Kohli (C), Ajinkya Rahane, Rishabh Pant (WK), Washington Sundar, Ravichandran Ashwin, Ishant Sharma, Jasprit Bumrah, Shahbaz Nadeem.
England (Playing XI) - Rory Burns, Dominic Sibley, Daniel Lawrence, Joe Root (C), Ben Stokes, Ollie Pope, Jos Buttler (WK), Dominic Bess, Jofra Archer, Jack Leach, James Anderson.

Virat Kohli, the Indian skipper, says that they would have batted first as well as the surface is a good one. Feels that it was an amazing phase as having a child is a different feeling and having the team won the series in Australia was the cherry on the top of the cake. Says that they have not thought about the WTC and that they focused on the process in Australia and it is important to focus on the present moment.

The England skipper, Joe Root, starts by saying that they will bat first and try to make the most of it. States that they will try to put up a good first innings total. Adds that he loves to play cricket in India and is looking forward to a great series. Tells that they need to play their best and they are confident.
TOSS - We are all in readiness for the toss. The men who matter, Joe Root and Virat Kohli are in the middle. Up goes the coin and it lands in the favor of Joe Root. ENGLAND WILL BAT FIRST!

England, on the other hand, comes into this series, with a 2-0 win against Sri Lanka in the Test series at the Island nation. They showed that they have what it takes for them to show their dominance in sub-continent conditions but to do it against this Indian team, who have lost just one Test in the period between November 2015 and November 2019 at home, will not be a walk in the park. But with Root's form, the inclusion of Stokes and Archer and with the reliable duo of James Anderson and Stuart Broad in their ranks, they certainly possess the tools to upset this Indian side. Will they able to pull a rabbit out of the hat or will this Indian team show their dominance on home soil and romp away to a victory? Join us for the toss and the team updates.

Talking about India, they have been on fire as they went Down Under and very famously have won the Border-Gavaskar Trophy 2020/21 with a very depleted squad. Doing something along those lines, that too with the squad that they possessed, must have given them so much confidence heading into this home tour. The return of Virat Kohli will be a massive boost to the hosts, and with the squad that they have, they will be gunning to start this Tour with a big win.

Hello, folks! We are welcoming international cricket to the Indian shores on this occasion as it is time for the sub-continent to welcome England for a pretty long tour which consists of 4 Tests, 5 T20Is and 3 ODIs. But first, they will contest in the purest form of the game as the Tests are upon us. On that note, let us give you a warm welcome to the first Test between these two giants which is being held in Chennai.

Right then. England now have to come out and bat and with the lead of 241 to their name, they will look to come out, score some runs quickly and swell that lead up to a big number, so that they can have a go at the Indians with the ball again. India will be hoping to scalp a few quick wickets and peg them on the back foot. We might also see a change in the batting line-up of England as they look to be aggressive. Join us for England's reply with the bat shortly.

England bowled wonderfully in the first innings. They bowled with intent and tested the batters well and their good work saw them peg four wickets very early on but were then pushed back by the duo of Pujara and Pant. But they came back strongly and removed them too and also saw off another fightback staged by the Sundar and Ashwin. Bess was the pick of the lot as he snared 4 wickets. Archer, Leach and Anderson scalped 2 wickets each to their name. Overall, just what Root would have wanted with the ball.

The batting by India did not start off nicely. They tried to keep the runs flowing by kept losing wickets at regular intervals and were not able to stitch those valuable partnerships. They were struggling at 73/4 at one point and even their charismatic skipper, Virat Kohli was back in the shed. Then came the fightback from the duo of Pujara and Pant stitched a great partnership of 119 runs before both of them fell one after the other and Pant fell while on 91 as well. Ashwin and Sundar then tried their best again, with a 80-run stand but once Ashwin fell, the wheels fell off and India was bundled for 337.

Good work by England after being pegged back in the first hour today has seen then bundle the Indians for a total of 337 and they also hold a massive lead of 241 to their name now and it has also been confirmed that they have not enforced the follow-on as well.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! What a stunning catch from Ben Stokes at first slip. Bumrah is unable to negotiate the two balls he was tasked to and India are bowled out. Fabulous catch from Stokes. Anderson bowls a full ball on off, the ball shapes away from Bumrah. Jasprit Bumrah looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge and it flies low to the right of first slip. Stokes there dives and takes a brilliant one-handed catch. INDIA BOWLED OUT FOR 337! Trail by 241!
Good shot and they take a run. Length ball around off, Sundar punches it to deep point and decides to take a run. 2 balls for Bumrah to face in this over.
Good length ball on off and middle, Washington defends it to the off side.
On middle, coming in with the angle. Sundar defends it to mid on with the angle.
Length ball on the pads, Sundar flicks it to square leg.

Good running and good over for India. Sundar manages to keep the strike and keep Bumrah away from the firing line. Darted full on the pads. A puff of dust pops off the pitch. Sundar taps it to the left of the bowler and takes a quick run.
Short and wide outside off, it spins a lot. Sundar leaves it alone.
Flatter wide outside off, Sundar cuts it but straight to backward point.
SIX! Smoked! Into the 80s now! Tossed up on off and middle, Sundar goes over Root's head and gets a biggie.
Good running! Flighted wide outside off, Sundar drives but he gets an inside edge which sees the ball go past the stumps. He calls for two and the pair is quick between the wickets and they get it.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Sundar will look to be aggressive now as he knows he is batting with a number 11. Floated outside off, Sundar goes aerial over extra cover and gets a boundary.
Joe Root to roll his arm now.
Full on off, Bumrah manages to defend it.

OUT! CAUGHT! James Anderson gets his first wicket of the game and Ishant's fight comes to an end. Excellent bowling from Anderson. Sets up the Indian tailender brilliantly. Full ball, followed by another full ball, puts Ishant on the front foot. Then Anderson unleashes a short ball. It is well-directed and more importantly, the ball does raise off the surface. Not an easy thing to do on a subcontinental Day 4 pitch. It is a cross-seam delivery. Ishant awkwardly plays at it and ends up giving a dolly to short leg. Ollie Pope there takes a simple catch. Indians need 56 runs to avoid the follow-on.
Jasprit Bumrah is the last man in for India.
Full on off, Ishant taps it back to the bowler.
Full on off, Ishant flicks it on the bounce to short leg.
Edged but safe! Fuller on off, Ishant looks to defend but gets an outside edge which goes to Burns at gully on a bounce.
Good shot! Length ball around off, Sundar punches it to deep point for one.
Tossed up on off and middle, Ishant keeps it out.
Short and spinning away outside off. Ishant shows great awareness and offers a good leave.
Flighted on middle, Sharma blocks it.
FOUR! Ishant getting aggressive now. A shot that has come out of the blue. Floated on middle, Sharma sweeps it in front of square on the leg side for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Ishant defends it.
Flighted on middle, Ishant uses his long stride and blocks it.

SIX! Dear, oh dear! Taken the aerial route, has Sundar. Moves into the 70s with his shot as well. Anderson bowls this one a good length and just around off, Sundar slams this one over the bowler's head and downtown for a biggie.
Sundar is not getting it to connect well. Length and outside off, Sundar looks to drive this one away but again fails to get any bat on this one.
Another delivery which is on a good length and outside the off pole, Sundar again looks to push this one away but he does not make any connection.
BEATEN! Another great ball by Sundar. On a good length again and just around off, Sundar looks for the defensive push away but he does not connect bat with ball.
PLAY AND A MISS! Sundar goes after this one but misses it. On a good length and outside off, Sundar looks to drive this one away but he misses his stroke completely.
Good length ball outside off, Sundar dabs this one towards the gully region.
Floated on middle, Ishant starts his innings with a solid block.
James Anderson is back into the attack.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nadeem departs and Leach gets his second of the day. What a difference a day makes! He was hammered left, right, and center by Pant on Day 3 but today Leach has been fantastic and gets another one. Slightly shorter on off, not too short just a tad. Nadeem gets on his back foot to defend but the ball turns away and takes the outside edge.  It just about carries to first slip and Stokes there manages to take a good catch. The extra man at silly point made him uncomfortable.
Tossed up on off, Nadeem blocks it uppishly. Lawrence at silly point is a bit away on the right. Had he been at traditional silly point, this could have been the end of Nadeem.
Ishant Sharma is the new batter in.
Floated on middle, Nadeem blocks it.
Flighted on off, Nadeem keeps it out and away from silly point.
Dom Sibley has called for a helmet as he gets ready to stand at silly point. Finally, Root has decided to keep both the short leg and silly point!

Hello and a warm welcome to Day 4 of this intriguing Test match between India and England. Against all the odds, the English Lions are on top after 3 days of play and are holding all the cards at the moment. First, they batted wonderfully, courtesy of a fine knock from their skipper, Root. Then they started very strongly with the ball and have snared 6 wickets and are leading by 321 runs. They will be looking to bundle the remaining wickets and enforce a follow-on whereas the Indians will be banking on Sundar and Ashwin to bat for as long as possible and take them to safer shores. Which team can achieve their goals? Join us as we bring you all the relevant updates...
... DAY 4, SESSION 1 ...

Right! That's all from the moving day of the game. England still in command in this game with a lead of more than 300. Now, on Day 4, how will the wicket behave? Can England strike early in the first session and push the Indians on the back foot? India would want these two to bat longer? Another exciting day on the cards. The action starts on Monday, 8th February, 2021 at 0930 local (0400 GMT). Join us then. For now, it is goodbye from our end.

England were pretty good with the ball throughout the day. It was Archer who gave them the breakthrough. He got the wicket of Rohit and Gill first and then it was all about Dom Bess. He got the big fish Kohli and then managed to remove Rahane too with Root taking a fine catch. He also got the wickets of Pujara and Pant. Overall, a decent effort. However, they would've loved a couple more on the day.

Earlier in the day, India managed to get the remaining two wickets of England in the first hour of the morning session. However, in the remaining overs, they lost their openers. Both the openers were looking good but failed to get going. Gill looked really good but departed to a fine catch. India then lost Kohli and Rahane in quick succession. Pant arrived and took the attack to the opposition. He hit 5 sixes in his 88-ball 91 with Pujara doing his work. The duo added 100-plus and kept India in the game. However, they too departed in quick time. Pujara got out in an unfortunate manner while Pant was dismissed going for a big shot. After that, Sundar and Ashwin managed to see off the threat while playing over 100 balls.

A battling day of Test cricket! A good effort from Sundar and Ashwin in this session to see off the threat. They have played over 100 balls and made sure England are not running away with the game. From 73 for 4 they have got to 257/6. However, they are still a long way behind in this game.

The physio is out now. Pujara was hit on the glove on the last ball of the last over. He looks to be in pain. Sips some liquid as the magic spray is applied to the affected part. He now seems good to continue.

Ouch! That's on the gloves. Pujara is in visible pain. He won't flinch though. He is got hit so many times on his body during India's tour to Australia. He got bruised but he continued the battle. And he will look to do so. Coming to the ball, this one pitches around off, it jags back in. A bit of extra bounce as well. Pujara looks to defend but the ball hits his gloves and goes on the leg side.
Back of a length and just outside off, poked towards point.
Good length and around off, Pant taps it towards cover for one.
Full and around off, Pant drives it towards mid off and calls for the single. He takes off but Puajra shouts loud no.
Good length and around middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! Nicely done! A good length ball outside off, Pant looks to defend. The ball takes the thick outside edge and goes between the slip and gully fielder. Races to the fence. Credit to Pant for playing it with soft hands.
Shortish and around off, kept out by Pujara
Outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Shortish and around off, Pujara taps it on the off side.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Short and wide outside off, Pujara looks to punch but mistimes it towards the cover region.
FOUR! Glorious from Pujara now! Full toss from Archer. Pujara drives it through mid on and it races away to the fence.
FOUR! Second boundary in the over. Pant continues to find the fence. Short and wide outside, Pant punches it on the up and through the covers for a boundary.
Good length and around off, Pant looks to defend. A hint of shape away. Just a hint. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to gully.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Shortish and around off, kept out.
Fuller and around middle and leg, kept out.
FOUR! THUMP! Short and wide outside off to begin from Anderson. Pant is quick to pounce on it. He flays it through cover-point for a boundary.
Who will partner Jofra at the other end? It will be the experienced James Anderson. Can he help England get a breakthrough here?
Fuller and on middle, it is flicked towards mid-wicket.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Slipped down the leg side on a fuller length. Pant flicks it to fine leg for one.
Fuller and around off, kept out by Pant.
Around off on a good length, Pant defends solidly again.
Good length and around off, Pant blocks.

Welcome back for the final session of the day. Cheteshwar Pujara and Rishabh Pant walk out to the middle. England players too are on the field now. They would be eyeing the wicket of Pant now? Can they cut the fiery southpaw's innings short? Jofra Archer to get the session going with the ball. Here he goes...
... DAY 3, SESSION 3 ...

So, the way Pant has batted in this session, the final one is set up nicely now. If he can continue the way he has in one more session, England will feel the heat a bit. However, one wicket for England and they will be into the bowling all-rounders. So, the most important session of the moving day coming up. Join us shortly for the same.

It was turning out to be a fantastic session for England with the ball. Bess bowled tightly and removed the Indian skipper cheaply. Rahane was sent packing, courtesy of a brilliant catch by England captain. Leach was smashed all over the park in his spell. However, England will be mighty pleased with their overall effort with the ball.

India started decently with Pujara and Kohli knocking the ball here and there. However, Kohli fell and Rahane followed his skipper. Pant arrived and went bang, bang. He has raced to a fine counter-attacking half ton and Pujara has set himself for a big one as well. Now, England are well ahead in this game at the moment but Pant with his style of play will surely made England think.

An entertaining session of cricket again! England struck twice after Lunch as the Kohli and Rahane fell early. Bess did superb stuff in this spell. Then came Pant and counter-attacked to make sure England are not completely on top of them.
Tossed up on off, Pujara dead bats it to the leg side .THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3!
Full and around off, Pujara comes down the track and pushes it to the  right of Bess. Dom runs to that side and fields it.
Tossed up on off, spinning into Pujara, he turns it to short leg.
Flatter and outside off, punched through covers for a single.
Tossed up around off, Pant defends it out off the front foot.
Tossed up outside off, driven to covers.
Tossed up on off, Pant gets to the pitch of the ball and then strokes it to long on for a single.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR PANT! A brilliant counter-attack from him. He has come like a flash here in the middle. He took Leach on as soon as he came to bowl and has raced to a half ton. Just 40 balls to get to his 5th half ton. What an innings from him so far. Leach tosses it wide outside off, Pant dances down and thumps it through mid off.
Full on middle, clipped to mid-wicket. A rare sight from Pant there.
Flatter outside off, Pujara cuts it to point for a single.
Round the wicket now to Pujara and he pads it away.

FOUR! 50 for Pujara! His 29th in Tests! 4th in his last 5 innings. Tossed up around off, Pujara gets to the pitch of the ball and then drives it through covers for a boundary to get to his milestone. What a time to get to it with the team in trouble. He needs to play a long inning.
Sharp spin there! Tossed up outside off, the ball spins away after pitching and Pant has not fuss in leaving it. England playing with Pant's patience. Can they scalp him before Tea?
Another tossed up ball going straight with the angle, Pant leaves it for Buttler.
Full on off, pushed straight to short cover.
Tossed up around off, Pant comes on the front foot and then defends it. He trusts the ball that it won't come into him.
Full and straight outside off, Pant lets it be.
FOUR! Lofted away! It's Bess' turn to take the beating now. Tossed up around off, Pant goes inside out and just clears the man there for a boundary.
On off, dabbed towards short third man. Looks for a single does Pujara but is sent back by Pant.

FOUR! Beautifully placed! Brilliant piece of timing on it! Tossed up around middle, Pujara skips down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a boundary. Leach trying to stem the run flow from his end.
Floated on off, kept out.
Flatter around off, Pujara pushes it to point there.
Flatter and outside off, Pujara slaps it towards third man. Bess now cuts it off. A couple once again.
On middle, whipped away towards fine leg. Sibley theremops it up as the batsmen take a brace.
Tossed up and around middle, clipped to deep mid-wicket for one.
On middle, pushed to mid on this time.
Full and around middle, flicked to mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! Pujara is safe on both the front. They check if it is bump ball first. Pujara is safe there and then comes the run out. He is back in with a dive. Floated around off and middle, Pujara comes down the track and flicks. Pope stops the ball to his left and throws the ball to the keeper. Buttler takes the bails off. An appeal is made. It is for a catch as well. The umpires get together. The soft signal for the catch is not out. Replays show that the ball is clearly bounced. Also, they now check the run out. Pujara is in. Direct hit would've been the end of Pujara.

Run out check sent upstairs! Pujara is the man in question and let's see what the replays have to say. Also, it is to check whether it is a bump ball. So, it is a bump ball first up. Pujara survives on that count. Now the run out. There also Pujara's dive has saved him. Pujara survives to fight it out for India.
Quicker one on the pads, tucked towards fine leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Flat and just outside off, left alone. 4-0-41-0. He has been taken to the cleaners by Pant.
Floated around off, Pujara keeps it out.
Flat and just outside off, poked towards point for one.
Flat and around middle, clipped to mid on for one.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed towards mid off for one.

SIX! Up and over! This man is just unbelievable. They have 5 men catching in the deep but Pant doesn't care. And Leach continues to teases him. Pant is down the track again. Goes for the shot. Clears Archer at long on who tries to catch but it goes over him. 4th six for Pant. A quick-fire 50-run stand comes up between these two.
Short and just around off, Pujara looks to pull but mistimes it towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed wide of the point fielder for one.
Short and around off, kept out.
Darted around off, a bit shortish length. Pant goes back to block.
Tossed up and outside off, driven to the right of the cover fielder who dives to his right and stops.
Floated around off, pushed to mid off.
Tossed up and just outside off, spins away. Left alone.
Tossed up and outside off, poked towards point.
Short and on middle and leg, clipped through square leg for one.
Short and wide, spinning away. Pujara guides it through short third man. The ball races to the fence. The fielder chases it down and saves one. Three taken.
Short and around middle, tucked away to deep square leg for one.
SIX! Take that! This is some confidence from Pant. Leach shows courage and tosses it up and around off, Pant accepts the offer, dances down the track and powers it over long on for a biggie.
Floated on off and middle, Pujara looks to defend it but ekes out an inside edge which drops in front of Ollie Pope at short leg. Another excellent over from Bess there.
On middle, punched off the back foot towards the leg side.
Fuller on off, Pujara goes on the back foot and defends it somehow.
Flatter and outside off, slapped towards deep cover for a single.
Floated on off, Pant defends it with  straight bat.
Tossed up and outside off, Pant shoulders arms to it.
Gets down and sweeps it down to deep square leg for one. 15 from the over.

SIX! And again! This time it wasn't too far away from the fielder there. Tossed up again from Leach. Pant comes down the track again. This time he is not to the pitch but goes with the shot. Fails to middle it but it is good enough to clear the fielder at deep mid-wicket. Lawrence tried to catch to his left but it goes away and over the fence.

SIX! There goes Pant! He doesn't care if you have a long on in place. Backs himself, comes down the track and Leach tosses it up and around off. Pant nails the slog over long on for a biggie. 100 up for India.
Big turn! Short and outside off, spins in. Pujara stays back and looks to defend. Inside edge, on the pad and it lobs. Buttler tries to catch but it drops away.
Full and just outside off, driven wide of mid off by Pujara for a single.

Pant shows his plans. He is not going to just block. There is a man at long on but he wants to clear him. Comes down the track and looks to go big. Mistimes it off the inner half down to long on. A single. Maybe he doesn't want Leach to settle.
Jack Leach comes back on. 1-0-6-0 from him.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries for Pujara. A solid shot. Bess tosses it up, Pujara puts the dancing shoes on again. Makes it a full toss and drills it through mid off.
FOUR! Nicely driven! Too full and Pujara drives it by coming down the track. He drives it hard through mid off for a boundary.
Floated outside off, Pujara comes down the track and pads it away.
Flat and spinning in. Pujara this time stays back and flicks. It is uppish but falls well short of the man at mid-wicket.
Comes down the track again, flicks and finds mid-wicket.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket by Pujara.
Full and wide outside off, another fluent drive from Pant but he finds mid off.
Full and around off, kept out.
Full and around off, Pant is solid in defense.
Fuller and outside off, Pant drives it towards mid off.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries. Another poor ball from Archer. He bowls it wide outside off and it is short in length. Pant reaches out and punches it through the covers for a boundary.
FOUR! On the pads on a fuller length, Pant flicks it down to the fine leg fence. Poor from Archer on the first ball.
Fuller on middle, Pujara whips it from around his legs but straight to mid-wicket.
On middle, defended to short mid-wicket off the back foot.
Floated around middle, defended to the leg side .
On middle, Pujara offers his pad as a mode of defense this time.
On middle, Pant clips it through mid-wicket. The fielder from mid-wicket chases the ball this the boundary and pulls it inside the ropes at the last instance. Pant gets off the mark with three runs.
Full on off, Pant dead bats it right under his eyes.
On middle, kept out by Pujara this time.
On middle, clipped to short square leg.
Fuller and outside off, Pujara shoulders arms at it once again.
Another one outside off, Pujara makes a leave once again.
Length and outside off, Pujara lifts his willow high and lets the ball go.
Length and around off, Pujara clips it towards square leg.
Jofra Archer again! 8-1-29-2 from him so far.
Flatter outside off, Pant slaps it straight to short cover. Another brilliant over from Dom Bess comes to an end. A wicket-maiden from him.
Floated on middle, Pant blocks it out from the crease once again.
Full on off, Pant dead bats it right under his eyes. It would be interesting to see how he places his game here.
Rishabh Pant joins Cheteshwar Pujara in the middle.

DRINKS! Two huge wickets for England. Skipper and his deputy has been sent packing. Pujara and Kohli were settlling in for a big stand but Bess got better of Kohli with a fine ball. Rahane fell to Bess again, but the spinner will thank skipper Root for taking that blinder. Indian on the back foot here in this game. Pujara will be key again. Interesting phase coming up.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is a stunner! Lovely catch from Root there. Bess into the game here. He first sends the captain and now the vice-captain. Tossed up around off, a bit of dip for Dom as Rahane tries to get to the pitch of the ball. He though chips it uppishly towards covers where Root put out his left hand and the ball sticks into his palm. India in all sorts of trouble with the top order back into the hut.
On middle, clipped to short leg.
Full and around off middle, Rahane goes for the flick but is not to the pitch of the ball as he hits it wide of Rory Burns at short mid-wicket.
A solid defensive stroke is what Pujara is known for and he plays one on this length ball around off from Anderson.
Now bowls a length ball outside off, Pujara does not play a stroke to it.
Length and around off, Pujara is rooted to his crease as he blocks it to short mid-wicket this time.
Fuller and around off, Pujara is solid in defense there.
Full and around middle, a slight inswing there as Rahane fends it away at the last instance towards deep backward square leg. He get off the mark with a single.
Fuller length ball on the pads of Pujara, he clips it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Floated on middle, Rahane dead bats it near his boots. Big over in the context of the game. A brilliant over from the young Dom Bess.
On middle, clipped away to the leg side by Rahane.
Ajinkya Rahane replaces skipper Kohli.

OUT! CAUGHT! Big, big wicket for England. Bess would be on cloud nine after that wicket. A dream wicket for him. Bess tosses this one up outside off and gets it to spin into Kohli. Virat comes on the front foot and goes to defend it away from the body. The ball catches the inside edge of his bat and lobs straight to Ollie Pope at short leg. Pope there gets to the ball and holds onto it. A fine catch from him. Bess is fired up. He will remember this wicket for a long time.
On middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Full and around off, Pujara comes on the front foot and then whips it to mid-wicket for a single.
Looped up on off, Pujara defends it to the on side.
And again! Kohli is not interested at anything that is wide outside off.
Wide outside off again, Kohli is not keen to play at it.
Outside off again, Kohli leaves again.
Another one in the channel outside off, Kohli makes another leave.
Fuller and around off, Kohli pushes it towards the cover region.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Full again, Pujara flicks powerfully. It is to the right of Bess who dives that side to keep it down to a dot.
Full and around middle, flicked to mid on.
Sharp turn. This one pitches outside off and spins in sharply. Pujara manages to get the bat down in time. It takes the inner half and hits his pad.
Low full toss, it is pushed to mid on. Kohli calls for the single. Pujara responds and they get it easily.
Short again, once again Kohli stays deep in his crase. He flicks but short leg makes a half stop. No run taken.
Flat and around middle, Kohli is on the back foot to block.
Very full and around off, Pujara keeps it out.
Outside off again from Anderson. This one swings late and comes in but Pujara has no issues leaving it alone.
Another one in the channel outside off, left alone again.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, pushed towards covers.
James Anderson is back on. 6-1-19-0 from him.
Full and around off, Pujara digs it out towards point and takes off for a single. Kohli says no. Pujara returns back.

In the air... just short. Risky from Kohli. Goes for the flick to this full ball without reaching to the pitch. There is a fielder at short mid-wicket, Rory Burns it is. He dives forward and looks to catch but it falls short.
On off, kept out.
Tossed up and around off, Pujara comes down the track and flicks it through square leg for one.
Shortish and around off, Kohli goes back and taps it in front of backward point for a run.
Flat and around off, Kohli goes back and blocks.
Floated around off, Kohli lunges forward and blocks.
Good length and around off, solidly kept out.
Bangs this one short. Pujara ducks.
Too full this time and Kohli pokes it towards point and gets to the other end.

Beats the outside edge of Kohli this time. Terrific from Archer. A hint of shape away from Archer. This is pitched just outside off, Kohli gets forward and looks to defend. The ball goes away just a touch but it is enough to beat the outside edge.
Good length and around off and middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.

Sharp bouncer from Archer. This one is around the body. Pujara looks to fend it off. The ball hits the gloves and it goes wide of the man at short leg. Fielder at leg gully would've gobbled this one. A single taken.
Flat again, it pitches around off and turns in again. Kolhi tucks it towards the man at short leg.
Flat and around off, Kohli stays back and blocks.
Floated just outside off, Kohli lunges forward and blocks.
Pujara comes down the track and tucks it towards square leg for one.
Floated around off, Pujara is solid in defense.
Loopy ball on middle, flicked to deep mid-wicket for one by Kohli.
Dom Bess comes into the attack. He just bowled one over before Lunch. It will be interesting to see how he goes about now.
Length and around middle, Pujara blocks it from within the crease there.
Full and in the driving zone for Pujara, Cheteshwar drives it but straight to mid off.
Still swing available. :Length and around off, moving away from Pujara. Cheteshwar shoulders arms to it.
Fuller once again from Jofra and Pujara pushes it from within the crease. It shaped a little bit there.
Length and angled on off, Pujara blocks it solidly towards mid on.
Fuller and in that channel of uncertainity and Pujara covers his sticks to let the ball through.
Once again the line is outside off from Anderson and Kohli does not fiddle with it.
Length and around off, Kohli taps it towards covers.
Length and around off, Kohli defends it to the leg side.
Another one in that channel well outside off, tempting Kohli to play the drive away from the body but the Indian skipper lets it be.
Length and outside off, Virat sees it and then decides to lift his willow to let the ball pass through.
Fuller and  in that channel around off, Kohli blocks it out to point once again.
Length and outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to it. Archer is nice in his groove there.
Full on off, Pujara gets down a bit low and then dead bats it down the track towards mid on.
Length and around middle, Kohli looks to clip it to the leg side but gets a soft leading edge towards cover-point for a single.
A nice defensive push on this length ball around off and Pujara gets a single.
Length and around off, Pujara guides it off the back foot towards backward point.
Full and wide outside off, almost a wide yorker and Pujara sees no need to play at it.
Jofra Archer from the other end.
Short of good length and around off, Kohli taps it off the back foot towards point. A good first over after Lunch from Anderson.
Full and on the pads, Kohli flicks it through mid-wicket and gets the session rolling with a couple.
Length and around off, Virat comes on the front foot and then defends it to point.
A fuller one targetting the stumps, Kophli opens his stance then defends it to cover-point.
Now bowls it on a length and around off, Kohli hops inside the crease and then pushes it to point.
Anderson speed in and bowls a fuller one around off, Kohli pushes it to  covers.

We are back for the second session of Day 3. Virat Kohli and Cheteshwar Pujara stride out to the middle as they look to lay a solid platform for India to scale the English total. The England players too are out in the middle and all set to begin. James Anderson will begin the session with the ball. Here we go...
... DAY 3, SESSION 2 ...

Pitch Report - Deep Dasgupta is down to share his insights on how the pitch will play post Lunch. He says that there is a little more rough on this wicket and the bowlers would try and use that against the right-handers. Adds that at the opposite, there are not many foot-marks and it is going to be interesting to see how the pitch plays post-Lunch.

So, a big session ahead now. India needs to bat long. Their two best Test batsmen are in the middle and they will look to take the team to a good position. England will know that another wicket early and they would be on top here. This what they will look to do. A very important session coming up. Join us for the same at 1210 local (0640 GMT).

Archer was brilliant with the ball in his first spell. He steamed in from start and got the reward. He bowled a few loose balls and Gill was quick to punish him. Archer got the wicket of Rohit first and then got Gill with Anderson helping him with a fine catch. They have not got a lot of support off the wicket and that can be seen with the scoring rate of India. However, with two wickets in the session with a big first inning score, they will be pleased with their performance.

Gill looked really good in the middle. He played a few top shots during his innings but fell to Archer. Rohit poked at a ball that he should've left and saw his downfall earlier in the Indian innings. Pujara has shown good intent in the middle and is looking good. Skipper Kohli has joined him and the duo now has a massive task in hand.

A fine session for England. Their overnight batters troubled the Indians for nearly an hour and scored 23 more runs before Ashwin removed the last man. And then Archer got both the Indian openers before they could get set for a big knock.
A fuller length and bit away from off, Pujara has no issues in leaving it. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Good length and in the channel around off, Pujara covers his sticks and lets it go though to Buttler.
short of good length and outside off, Pujara is watchful as he defends it to the off side.
Good length and around off, Pujara keeps it out off the front foot.

Beaten! Leg cutter from Stokes and it is bowled on length too. The ball is in the channel outside off, Pujara goes to feel for the ball but gets beaten on the movement there. The ball dies down on its way to the keeper.
Length and around off, Pujara plays a compact front foot defense.
Ben Stokes is back on.
Quicker and fuller outside off, Kohli taps it down the track off the back foot.
Tossed up around off, Kohli lunges froward and defends it out.
Floated on midlde, Pujara waits for the ball to come and then turns it towards square leg for a single.
Floated on middle, Pujara whips it to short mid-wicket.
On off, Pujara blocks it out to short leg.
Loopy delivery on the pads first up from Bess, Kohli strokes it down to long on for a single.
Spin from both the ends now. Dom Bess will roll his arms now.
Now, he brings a solid front foot defence on this tossed up ball around off does Pujara.
FOUR! Terrific shot! Floated on leg, Pujara skips down the track and then whips it towards deep mid-wicket as the ball crosses the fence there.
Some turn for Jack Leach! Tossed up around off, Kohli pushes it off the back foot through cover-point for a single.
Flatter and around off, Kohli pushes it to backward point now.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Pujara cuts it to deep point and scampers for a single.
Floated around middle, Pujara pushes it off the front foot towards mid-wicket.
Time for spin! Here is Jack Leach with the ball. Slip and short leg in place.
Shortish and on middle, Kohli tucks it towards the man at short leg.
Short of good length around middle, Kohli looks to drop it off the back foot towards the leg side but ends up dropping it near his boots.
Short and down leg, Kohli ducks under it.
Short of good length around off, Pujara drops it in front of covers and gets a single.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and outside off, Pujara flays at it and gets it in the gap through point for a boundary. 50-up for India.
Short one on middle, Kohli rides the bounce and then pulls it to short leg. The man there misfields as the ball goes to square leg for a single.
A ripper to end the over, a successful one again from Archer. Just outside off on a good length, Pujara looks to defend but is beaten. Lucky not to edge behind.

Sharp stuff from Archer. He's steaming in. He once again bangs it short and on the body. Kohli gets on his toes and looks to fend it off. It bounces extra and goes wide of the short leg off the handle. A single taken and Kohli is off the mark in a streaky manner.
Bangs short this time and Kohli ducks under it.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
Super V, Virat Kohli comes out to bat now.

OUT! TAKEN! Anderson with a stunning catch at mid on. Archer gets his man. Both the openers dismissed for India now. A fuller ball from Anderson. Gill punches the drive uppishly. He does that half-heartedly. The ball goes uppishly towards mid on. Anderson there quickly moves to his left and lunges forward to take the low catch. A fine catch from the veteran. His 97th catch in Tests. A solid knock from Gill but he will be disappointed. A fine track for batting but he falls.
FOUR! Punished again! Full again from Archer and Gill flicks it nonchalantly through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Short again from Stokes and Gill pulls it through square leg for one.
Banged short and on middle, Gill sits under it.
Good length and outside off, Pujara drops it in front of the cover region for a single.
Short ball around middle, kept out.
Shortish and just outside off, Pujara drops his wrists and lets it go.
Short ball from Stokes to begin. Gill pulls it towards deep square leg for a run.
Ben Stokes replaces James Anderson now.

Shubman Gill getting some attention from the physio. He was struck on the glove on the previous delivery from Archer. He looks to be in some as some bandaging done on his right hand. The good thing for India is that he will continue.

Ouch! Extra bounce for Archer there. A length ball around middle and leg, Gill looks to work it on the leg side. The extra bounce means the ball hits his glove and goes towards square leg. A single taken.
A sharp bouncer from Archer. It is around off, Gill drops his wrists and lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball around middle, tucked towards square leg for one.
